# Playwright E2E Rules

## Setup

- Config: `playwright.config.ts` — baseURL `http://localhost:3000`, auto-starts `npm run dev`
- Tests live in `tests/e2e/*.spec.ts`
- Run: `npm run test:e2e` (UI mode: `npm run test:e2e:ui`)

**Prerequisites:** FE dev server + BE at `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` (default `http://localhost:5255/api`) with seeded accounts.

## Screen ID Mapping

Name tests after TASKS IDs: `M-01`, `W-02`, etc. Match `docs/TASKS.md` / `docs/TASKS_VU.md`.

| Spec file | Portal | Login route |
|---|---|---|
| `manager.spec.ts` | Manager | `/auth/internal` |
| `washer.spec.ts` | Washer | `/auth/internal` |

## Auth in Tests

```typescript
const EMAIL = process.env.PLAYWRIGHT_MANAGER_EMAIL || 'manager1@autowashpro.com'
const PASSWORD = process.env.PLAYWRIGHT_MANAGER_PASSWORD || 'Admin@123'

await page.goto('/auth/internal')
await page.fill('input[id="email"]', EMAIL)
await page.fill('input[id="password"]', PASSWORD)
await page.click('button[type="submit"]')
await page.waitForURL('**/manager') // or **/washer
```

Credentials can be overridden via `.env.local` — see `.env.example`.

## Assertions

- Prefer Vietnamese UI text: `toContainText('Quản lý slot', { ignoreCase: true })`
- Assert no crash on dynamic IDs (`/manager/booking/1`) — friendly error OK
- Use `page.locator('body')` for smoke checks; tighten selectors when stabilizing

## Do Not

- Hardcode secrets in spec files — use env vars with safe defaults
- Leave `test.only` in committed code (`forbidOnly` on CI)
- Assume mock data — E2E hits real API through the running app
